Q1.
[BASIC] You have an Employees table with columns: employee_id, first_name, salary, and hire_date. Write a SQL query to retrieve the first_name and salary of all employees who were hired after January 1, 2024, and order the results by salary in descending order.
ANS
SELECT first_name, salary FROM Employees WHERE hire_date > '2024-01-01' ORDER BY salary DESC;
